* Roland Kaminski <kaminski@cs.uni-potsdam.de>
  

if you want to just have a look and run something, maybe try:
- https://potassco.org/clingo/run/

Otherwise, I list some reading material below:

- Answer Set Programming at a Glance
https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1145/2043174.2043195

- Answer Set Programming: A Primer
http://www.kr.tuwien.ac.at/staff/tkren/pub/2009/rw2009-asp.pdf

- Answer Set Programming
https://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/vl/teaching/378/ASP.pdf

- AI Magazine Special Issue on Answer Set Programming
https://www.aaai.org/ojs/index.php/aimagazine/issue/view/215

- Our guide:
https://github.com/potassco/guide/releases/tag/v2.2.0

* I found the textbook Knowledge Representation, Reasoning, and the Design of Intelligent Agents by Gelfond and Kahl particularly helpful first look at ASP. https://www.amazon.com/Knowledge-Representation-Reasoning-Design-Intelligent/dp/1107029562
